<dl id="n56289a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56289a">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56289a"> 289(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pilgrim</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The water flowing from these mountains is the same as the heavenly liquid of immortality; it is said that the divine rivers are receptacles for hundreds of places of pilgrimage. <small> Heinrich Zimmer, <a name="HZMI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#HZMI"><cite title="source">Maya der indische Mythos</cite></a> (1936) 102</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
